{
  "texts": [
    "FeasibilityTwelve studies from eight countries contributed to these findings (USA, Canada, UK, Australia, England, Scotland, Nigeria, Chile).",
    "Participants in seven studies were all over 60 [53,77,80,84,91,95,96].",
    "Three studies had participants with a mean or average age of 60 or older [78,79,92] and two studies were from LMICs or vulnerable populations of which both were included based on a lowered age threshold [81][82][83].",
    "In 10 of the studies most of the participants where women (62-100%) [53, 77-82, 84, 91, 95, 96].",
    "In two studies there was about an equal distribution between men and women [83,92]."
  ]
}